nd the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBuddhism and science. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Buddhist.2bisacsh1 aBitbol, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidson, Richard J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimidjian, Sona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoty, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurant, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasenkamp, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasenkamp, Wendy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJinpa, Thupten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasturirangan, Rajesh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoch, Christof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNamgyal, Geshe Dadul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNegi, Geshe Lobsang Tenzin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRicard, Matthieu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSamten, Geshe Ngawang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSinger, Tania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStern, Aaron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhite, Janna R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhite, Janna R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZajonc, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe 